The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Train push
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Train push
                            
	Bandel ( Hooghly), April 17: A girl was killed after being allegedly thrown off a running train by her boyfriend near Bandal tonight.         
	Akbar Ali, 20, a worker at a plastic factory in North-24 Parganas Naihati, was standing near the door of a compartment with Shahjadi Khatun, 18, when he suddenly pushed her off the train, police said.         
	They said Ali had a quarrel with Khatun before boarding the train from Bandel at 8.40pm.        
	Co-passengers handed Ali to the railway police.                                                                                                                                                             
